{"title_page": "NAM Air", "text_new": "{{Infobox Airline\n|airline=NAM Air\n|logo=LOGO NAM HORIZONTAL.png\n|logo_size=250px\n|IATA=IN\n|ICAO=LKN\n|callsign=NAMAIR<ref>{{cite web|title=JO 7340.2J Contractions - Basic with Change 1 & Change 2|url=https://www.faa.gov/documentLibrary/media/Order/7340.2J_Basic_w_Chg_1_and_2_dtd_1_30_20.pdf|website=Federal Aviation Administration|accessdate=12 February 2020|pages=3-1-70, 3-2-53, 3-3-49|date=3 June 2019}}</ref>\n|parent= [[Sriwijaya Air]]\n|founded={{start date and age|2013}}\n|commenced={{start date and age|2013|12|11|df=y}}\n|headquarters=Jakarta, Indonesia\n|key_people=Jefferson Jauwena, CEO\nChandra Lie, President Commissioner\n|hubs={{fact|date=September 2019}}{{plainlist|\n*[[Soekarno-Hatta International Airport]]\n*[[Juanda International Airport]]\n*[[Supadio Airport]]\n}}\n|focus_cities={{fact|date=September 2019}}{{plainlist|\n*[[Adisucipto International Airport]]\n*[[Sultan Mahmud Badaruddin II International Airport]]\n*[[Silampari Airport]]\n*[[Ngurah Rai International Airport]]\n}}\n|frequent_flyer=\n|lounge=\n|alliance=\n| subsidiaries   = \n|fleet_size= 16\n|destinations=21\n| company_slogan =\n|website={{URL|http://www.flynamair.com}}\n}}\n\n'''NAM Air''' is an Indonesian [[airline]] based in [[Jakarta]] that commenced its operation on 11 December 2013. Headquartered in [[Central Jakarta]], the airline acting as feeder of its parent company, [[Sriwijaya Air]], using 10 B737-500 Winglets with 8 Executive Class seats and 112 Economy Class seats and 5 ATR-72-600s. In 26 September 2013, its parent company Sriwijaya Air announces for purchasing up to 100 [[IPTN N-250|R-80]] regional planes for its future operations. The airline is listed as a Category 1 airline by Indonesia's [[Civil Aviation Authority]], the highest status that can be achieved for operational safety.\n\n==History==\nIn its original plan, NAM Air had been projected as a full-service airline carrier to compete with [[Garuda Indonesia]] and [[Lion Air]]'s full-service arm, Space Jet Aviation, later renamed [[Batik Air]]. This plan was scrapped and changed to a feeder for Sriwijaya Air having the same scheme as what  Lion Air with its [[Wings Air]] has currently, and, in the 1990s, Garuda Indonesia with [[Merpati]]. Sriwijaya Air serves main routes, while NAM Air serves its secondary routes.<ref name=\"Sriwijaya Dirikan Maskapai Full Service Nam Air\">{{cite web|title=Sriwijaya Dirikan Maskapai Full Service Nam Air|url=http://indo-aviation.com/2012/09/12/sriwijaya-dirikan-maskapai-full-service-nam-air/|website=Indo-aviation.com}}</ref>\n[[File:NAM Air.jpg|thumb|Boeing 737-500 landing at [[Ngurah Rai International Airport|Bali's Airport]]]]\nOn 26 September 2013, NAM Air was officially introduced as a subsidiary of Sriwijaya Air planned on having its first flight on October 2013; a plan later postponed because AOC had not been issued by the Indonesia Ministry of Transportation. NAM Air acquired its AOC on 29 November 2013 and flew its maiden flight from Jakarta to Pangkal Pinang on 11 December 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=NAM Air Terbang Perdana 11-12-2013|url=http://bangka.tribunnews.com/2013/12/12/nam-air-terbang-perdana-11-12-2013|website=bangka.tribunnews.com/}}</ref> First commercial flight later follows from Jakarta to Pontianak, and Pontianak to Yogyakarta in 19 December 2013.<ref>{{cite news|title=Hari Ini NAM Air Terbang Perdana|url=http://bisniskeuangan.kompas.com/read/2013/12/19/0744380/Hari.Ini.NAM.Air.Terbang.Perdana.|publisher=Kompas.com|date=19 December 2013}}</ref>\n\nNAM Air is named after Chandra Lie's father, Lo Kui Nam.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nam Air, Persembahan Chandra Lie untuk Sang Ayah|url=http://idsaham.com/news-saham-Nam-Air-Persembahan-Chandra-Lie-untuk-Sang-Ayah-378938.html|website=swa.co.id archived by idsaham.com|accessdate=30 June 2017}}</ref> The NAM acronym has also been used by other Sriwijaya Air group of companies: National Aviation Management (Flying School-better known as NAM Flying School), National Aircrew Management (Cabin Crew Training Center), National Aircraft Maintenance (Aircraft Maintenance)and Negeri Aksara Mandiri (In-flight Magazine).\n\nFounded in 2013, NAM Air is the first and only airline in Indonesia that allows female flight attendants to wear [[hijab]] in all regular flights, followed by its parent company, Sriwijaya Air, in November 2015. This has made them to become a few of those airlines to do so in Southeast Asia alongside  [[Royal Brunei Airlines]]. Other airlines in Indonesia only allow their female flight attendants to use hijab when flying Hajj/Umra flights or flights to Middle East especially to Saudi Arabia.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kecantikan Pramugari Berhijab di Maskapai NAM Air|url=http://news.detik.com/berita/2871007/kecantikan-pramugari-berhijab-di-maskapai-nam-air|website=detik.com}}</ref>\n\n== Destinations ==\nNAM Air flies domestic routes in Indonesia, and has one international flight to Dili. List of routes flown by NAM Air:<ref>[http://travel.kompas.com/read/2017/10/17/100800027/sriwijaya-dan-nam-air-permudah-wisatawan-ke-raja-ampat Sriwijaya dan NAM Air Permudah Wisatawan ke Raja Ampat]</ref>\n\n;Indonesia\n*'''[[Java]]''' and '''[[Lesser Sunda Islands]]'''\n**[[Alor Island]] - ([[Mali Airport]])\n**[[Bali]] - ([[Ngurah Rai International Airport]])<ref>http://m.rri.co.id/surakarta/post/berita/788867/ekonomi/nam_air_pindah_rute_penerbangan_dari_solo_mana_saja_rutenya.html</ref><ref>https://m.solopos.com/nam-air-buka-rute-anyar-dari-bandara-adi-soemarmo-ke-luar-jawa-mana-saja-1046501</ref><ref>https://www.flynamair.com/admin/assets/uploads/images/home_banner/2020-03/terbang-solo-3-en-7161.jpg</ref>\n**[[Bajawa]] - ([[Turelelo Soa Airport]])\n**[[Bima]] - ([[Sultan Muhammad Salahudin Airport]])\n**[[Ende, East Nusa Tenggara|Ende]] - ([[H. Hasan Aroeboesman Airport]])\n**[[Jakarta]] - ([[Soekarno-Hatta International Airport]])<ref>https://www.flynamair.com/about</ref><ref>https://jambi.antaranews.com/berita/308789/seputar-nam-air-yang-patut-anda-ketahui</ref>\n**[[Labuan Bajo]] - ([[Komodo Airport]])\n**[[Kupang]] - ([[El Tari International Airport]])\n**[[Maumere]] - ([[Frans Xavier Seda Airport]])\n**[[Ruteng]] - ([[Frans Sales Lega Airport]])\n**[[Semarang]] - ([[Achmad Yani International Airport]])\n**[[Surakarta]] - ([[Adisumarmo International Airport]])<ref>http://m.rri.co.id/surakarta/post/berita/788867/ekonomi/nam_air_pindah_rute_penerbangan_dari_solo_mana_saja_rutenya.html</ref><ref>https://m.solopos.com/nam-air-buka-rute-anyar-dari-bandara-adi-soemarmo-ke-luar-jawa-mana-saja-1046501</ref><ref>https://www.flynamair.com/admin/assets/uploads/images/home_banner/2020-03/terbang-solo-3-en-7161.jpg</ref>\n**[[Surabaya]] - ([[Juanda International Airport]])\n**[[Tambolaka]] - ([[Tambolaka Airport]])\n**[[Waingapu]] - ([[Umbu Mehang Kunda Airport]])\n**[[Yogyakarta]] - ([[Adisucipto International Airport]])<ref>https://www.jogja.tribunnews.com/amp/2013/12/20/nam-air-kini-terbangi-rute-yogyakarta-pontianak</ref><ref>https://www.flynamair.com/about</ref><ref>https://jambi.antaranews.com/berita/308789/seputar-nam-air-yang-patut-anda-ketahui</ref> (Terminated Since 31 March, 2020)\n*'''[[Sumatra]]''' and '''[[Riau Islands]]'''\n**[[Bandar Lampung]] - ([[Radin Inten II Airport]])\n**[[Lubuklinggau]] - ([[Silampari Airport]])\n**[[Palembang]] - ([[Sultan Mahmud Badaruddin II International Airport]])<ref>http://m.rri.co.id/surakarta/post/berita/788867/ekonomi/nam_air_pindah_rute_penerbangan_dari_solo_mana_saja_rutenya.html</ref><ref>https://m.solopos.com/nam-air-buka-rute-anyar-dari-bandara-adi-soemarmo-ke-luar-jawa-mana-saja-1046501</ref><ref>https://www.flynamair.com/admin/assets/uploads/images/home_banner/2020-03/terbang-solo-3-en-7161.jpg</ref>\n**[[Pangkal Pinang]] - ([[Depati Amir Airport]])<ref>http://m.rri.co.id/surakarta/post/berita/788867/ekonomi/nam_air_pindah_rute_penerbangan_dari_solo_mana_saja_rutenya.html</ref><ref>https://m.solopos.com/nam-air-buka-rute-anyar-dari-bandara-adi-soemarmo-ke-luar-jawa-mana-saja-1046501</ref><ref>https://www.flynamair.com/admin/assets/uploads/images/home_banner/2020-03/terbang-solo-3-en-7161.jpg</ref>\n**[[Tanjung Pandan]] - ([[H.A.S. Hanandjoeddin International Airport]])\n*'''[[Kalimantan]]'''\n**[[Banjarmasin]] - ([[Syamsudin Noor Airport]]) <ref>https://www.kompas.com/money/read/2019/04/26/112844326/nam-air-buka-2-rute-baru-di-kalimantan-mulai-1-mei-2019</ref>\n**[[Ketapang (Kalimantan)|Ketapang]] - ([[Rahadi Osman Airport]])<ref>https://www.instagram.com/p/BabSfbRDty5/</ref>\n**[[Palangkaraya]] - ([[Tjilik Riwut Airport]])<ref>http://m.rri.co.id/surakarta/post/berita/788867/ekonomi/nam_air_pindah_rute_penerbangan_dari_solo_mana_saja_rutenya.html</ref><ref>https://m.solopos.com/nam-air-buka-rute-anyar-dari-bandara-adi-soemarmo-ke-luar-jawa-mana-saja-1046501</ref>\n**[[Pangkalan Bun]] - ([[Iskandar Airport]])\n**[[Pontianak, Indonesia|Pontianak]] - ([[Supadio International Airport]])<ref>https://www.kompas.com/money/read/2019/04/26/112844326/nam-air-buka-2-rute-baru-di-kalimantan-mulai-1-mei-2019</ref><ref>https://www.flynamair.com/about</ref><ref>https://jambi.antaranews.com/berita/308789/seputar-nam-air-yang-patut-anda-ketahui</ref><ref>https://www.instagram.com/p/BabSfbRDty5/</ref><ref>https://www.jogja.tribunnews.com/amp/2013/12/20/nam-air-kini-terbangi-rute-yogyakarta-pontianak</ref><ref>http://m.rri.co.id/surakarta/post/berita/788867/ekonomi/nam_air_pindah_rute_penerbangan_dari_solo_mana_saja_rutenya.html</ref><ref>https://m.solopos.com/nam-air-buka-rute-anyar-dari-bandara-adi-soemarmo-ke-luar-jawa-mana-saja-1046501</ref><ref>https://www.flynamair.com/admin/assets/uploads/images/home_banner/2020-03/terbang-solo-3-en-7161.jpg</ref>\n**[[Putussibau]] - ([[Pangsuma Airport]])<ref>https://www.instagram.com/p/BabSfbRDty5/</ref>\n**[[Samarinda]] - ([[Aji Pangeran Tumenggung Pranoto Airport]]) <ref>https://www.kompas.com/money/read/2019/04/26/112844326/nam-air-buka-2-rute-baru-di-kalimantan-mulai-1-mei-2019</ref>\n**[[Sampit]] - ([[Sampit Airport]])\n**[[Sintang Regency|Sintang]] - ([[Tebelian Airport]])<ref>https://www.instagram.com/p/BabSfbRDty5/</ref>\n**[[Tarakan]] - ([[Juwata International Airport]]) <ref>https://www.kompas.com/money/read/2019/04/26/112844326/nam-air-buka-2-rute-baru-di-kalimantan-mulai-1-mei-2019</ref>\n*'''[[Sulawesi]]''' and '''[[Maluku Islands|Maluku]]'''\n**[[Ambon, Maluku|Ambon]] - ([[Pattimura Airport]])\n**[[Manado]] - ([[Sam Ratulangi International Airport]])\n**[[Ternate]] - ([[Sultan Babullah Airport]])\n*'''[[West Papua (province)|West Papua]]''' and '''[[Papua (province)|Papua]]'''\n**[[Biak]] - ([[Frans Kaisiepo Airport]])\n**[[Fakfak]] - ([[Fakfak Torea Airport]])\n**[[Jayapura]] - ([[Sentani Airport]])\n**[[Kaimana]] - ([[Utarom Airport]])\n**[[Waisai]] - ([[Marinda Airport]])\n\n;East Timor\n*[[Dili]] - ([[Presidente Nicolau Lobato International Airport]]) <ref> https://m.bisnis.com/amp/read/20151220/98/503517/nam-air-buka-rute-baru-denpasar-dili</ref>\n\n== Fleet ==\n[[File:NAM Air Sintang.jpg|thumb|NAM Air ATR 72-600 at [[Tebelian Airport]], [[Sintang Regency|Sintang]]]]\n[[File:PK-NAP.jpg|thumb|NAM Air Boeing 737-500 at [[Ngurah Rai International Airport]], [[Denpasar]].]]\nThe NAM Air fleet consists of the following aircraft (as of August 2019):<ref>{{cite journal|title=Global Airline Guide 2019 (Part One)|journal=Airliner World|issue=October 2019|page=16}}</ref>\n\n<center>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"3\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse;text-align:center\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Aircraft\n! rowspan=\"2\" |In Service\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Orders \n! colspan=\"3\" |Passengers\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Notes\n|-\n!C\n!Y\n!Total\n|-\n|[[ATR 72|ATR 72-600]]\n|5<ref>https://www.instagram.com/p/BeF1b5jH5r7/</ref>\n|1\n|0\n|72\n|72 \n|\n|-\n|[[Boeing 737 Classic|Boeing 737-500]]\n|11\n|&mdash;\n|8\n|112\n|120\n|\n|-\n!Total\n!16\n!1\n!colspan=\"4\"|\n|}\n</center>\n\nEvery Sriwijaya Air Group plane (which includes NAM Air) has a unique name, which can be seen on the nose section. The names are taken from holy book phrases, places, behaviours, and plants or birds. Examples on NAM Air include \"Bersinar\" (Shiny), \"Kehormatan\" (Honor), and \"Berbagi (Sharing).\n\n==EU aviation blacklist==\n{{main|List of air carriers banned in the European Union}}\nNAM Air was banned from operating in European airspace,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ec.europa.eu/transport/modes/air/safety/air-ban/index_en.htm|title=The EU Air Safety List - Transport|publisher=}}</ref><ref>http://ec.europa.eu/transport/modes/air/safety/air-ban/doc/list_en.pdf</ref> appearing on a list of carriers that did not meet necessary safety standards to fly to airports in the European Union. It was removed from the blacklist, along with every other Indonesian airline on 14 June 2018.<ref>{{cite web |last1=European Commission |title=Aviation Safety: Commission removes all airlines from Indonesia from EU Air Safety List |url=http://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_IP-18-4131_en.htm |website=European Commission - Press Release Database |accessdate=10 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category|NAM Air}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.flynamair.com}}\n\n{{Portalbar|Indonesia|Companies|Aviation}}\n{{Garuda Indonesia}}\n{{Airlines of Indonesia}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sriwijaya Air Destinations}}\n[[Category:Airlines banned in the European Union]]\n[[Category:Airlines of Indonesia]]\n[[Category:Airlines established in 2013]]\n[[Category:2013 establishments in Indonesia]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Airline\n|airline=NAM Air\n|logo=LOGO NAM HORIZONTAL.png\n|logo_size=250px\n|IATA=IN\n|ICAO=LKN\n|callsign=NAMAIR<ref>{{cite web|title=JO 7340.2J Contractions - Basic with Change 1 & Change 2|url=https://www.faa.gov/documentLibrary/media/Order/7340.2J_Basic_w_Chg_1_and_2_dtd_1_30_20.pdf|website=Federal Aviation Administration|accessdate=12 February 2020|pages=3-1-70, 3-2-53, 3-3-49|date=3 June 2019}}</ref>\n|parent= [[Sriwijaya Air]]\n|founded={{start date and age|2013}}\n|commenced={{start date and age|2013|12|11|df=y}}\n|headquarters=Jakarta, Indonesia\n|key_people=Jefferson Jauwena, CEO\nChandra Lie, President Commissioner\n|hubs={{fact|date=September 2019}}{{plainlist|\n*[[Soekarno-Hatta International Airport]]\n*[[Juanda International Airport]]\n*[[Supadio Airport]]\n}}\n|focus_cities={{fact|date=September 2019}}{{plainlist|\n*[[Adisucipto International Airport]]\n*[[Sultan Mahmud Badaruddin II International Airport]]\n*[[Silampari Airport]]\n*[[Ngurah Rai International Airport]]\n}}\n|frequent_flyer=\n|lounge=\n|alliance=\n| subsidiaries   = \n|fleet_size= 16\n|destinations=21\n| company_slogan =\n|website={{URL|http://www.flynamair.com}}\n}}\n\n'''NAM Air''' is an Indonesian [[airline]] based in [[Jakarta]] that commenced its operation on 11 December 2013. Headquartered in [[Central Jakarta]], the airline acting as feeder of its parent company, [[Sriwijaya Air]], using 10 B737-500 Winglets with 8 Executive Class seats and 112 Economy Class seats and 5 ATR-72-600s. In 26 September 2013, its parent company Sriwijaya Air announces for purchasing up to 100 [[IPTN N-250|R-80]] regional planes for its future operations. The airline is listed as a Category 1 airline by Indonesia's [[Civil Aviation Authority]], the highest status that can be achieved for operational safety.\n\n==History==\nIn its original plan, NAM Air had been projected as a full-service airline carrier to compete with [[Garuda Indonesia]] and [[Lion Air]]'s full-service arm, Space Jet Aviation, later renamed [[Batik Air]]. This plan was scrapped and changed to a feeder for Sriwijaya Air having the same scheme as what  Lion Air with its [[Wings Air]] has currently, and, in the 1990s, Garuda Indonesia with [[Merpati]]. Sriwijaya Air serves main routes, while NAM Air serves its secondary routes.<ref name=\"Sriwijaya Dirikan Maskapai Full Service Nam Air\">{{cite web|title=Sriwijaya Dirikan Maskapai Full Service Nam Air|url=http://indo-aviation.com/2012/09/12/sriwijaya-dirikan-maskapai-full-service-nam-air/|website=Indo-aviation.com}}</ref>\n[[File:NAM Air.jpg|thumb|Boeing 737-500 landing at [[Ngurah Rai International Airport|Bali's Airport]]]]\nOn 26 September 2013, NAM Air was officially introduced as a subsidiary of Sriwijaya Air planned on having its first flight on October 2013; a plan later postponed because AOC had not been issued by the Indonesia Ministry of Transportation. NAM Air acquired its AOC on 29 November 2013 and flew its maiden flight from Jakarta to Pangkal Pinang on 11 December 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=NAM Air Terbang Perdana 11-12-2013|url=http://bangka.tribunnews.com/2013/12/12/nam-air-terbang-perdana-11-12-2013|website=bangka.tribunnews.com/}}</ref> First commercial flight later follows from Jakarta to Pontianak, and Pontianak to Yogyakarta in 19 December 2013.<ref>{{cite news|title=Hari Ini NAM Air Terbang Perdana|url=http://bisniskeuangan.kompas.com/read/2013/12/19/0744380/Hari.Ini.NAM.Air.Terbang.Perdana.|publisher=Kompas.com|date=19 December 2013}}</ref>\n\nNAM Air is named after Chandra Lie's father, Lo Kui Nam.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nam Air, Persembahan Chandra Lie untuk Sang Ayah|url=http://idsaham.com/news-saham-Nam-Air-Persembahan-Chandra-Lie-untuk-Sang-Ayah-378938.html|website=swa.co.id archived by idsaham.com|accessdate=30 June 2017}}</ref> The NAM acronym has also been used by other Sriwijaya Air group of companies: National Aviation Management (Flying School-better known as NAM Flying School), National Aircrew Management (Cabin Crew Training Center), National Aircraft Maintenance (Aircraft Maintenance)and Negeri Aksara Mandiri (In-flight Magazine).\n\nFounded in 2013, NAM Air is the first and only airline in Indonesia that allows female flight attendants to wear [[hijab]] in all regular flights, followed by its parent company, Sriwijaya Air, in November 2015. This has made them to become a few of those airlines to do so in Southeast Asia alongside  [[Royal Brunei Airlines]]. Other airlines in Indonesia only allow their female flight attendants to use hijab when flying Hajj/Umra flights or flights to Middle East especially to Saudi Arabia.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kecantikan Pramugari Berhijab di Maskapai NAM Air|url=http://news.detik.com/berita/2871007/kecantikan-pramugari-berhijab-di-maskapai-nam-air|website=detik.com}}</ref>\n\n== Destinations ==\nNAM Air flies domestic routes in Indonesia, and has one international flight to Dili. List of routes flown by NAM Air:<ref>[http://travel.kompas.com/read/2017/10/17/100800027/sriwijaya-dan-nam-air-permudah-wisatawan-ke-raja-ampat Sriwijaya dan NAM Air Permudah Wisatawan ke Raja Ampat]</ref>\n\n;Indonesia\n*'''[[Java]]''' and '''[[Lesser Sunda Islands]]'''\n**[[Alor Island]] - ([[Mali Airport]])\n**[[Bali]] - ([[Ngurah Rai International Airport]])<ref>http://m.rri.co.id/surakarta/post/berita/788867/ekonomi/nam_air_pindah_rute_penerbangan_dari_solo_mana_saja_rutenya.html</ref><ref>https://m.solopos.com/nam-air-buka-rute-anyar-dari-bandara-adi-soemarmo-ke-luar-jawa-mana-saja-1046501</ref><ref>https://www.flynamair.com/admin/assets/uploads/images/home_banner/2020-03/terbang-solo-3-en-7161.jpg</ref>\n**[[Bajawa]] - ([[Turelelo Soa Airport]])\n**[[Bima]] - ([[Sultan Muhammad Salahudin Airport]])\n**[[Ende, East Nusa Tenggara|Ende]] - ([[H. Hasan Aroeboesman Airport]])\n**[[Jakarta]] - ([[Soekarno-Hatta International Airport]])<ref>https://www.flynamair.com/about</ref><ref>https://jambi.antaranews.com/berita/308789/seputar-nam-air-yang-patut-anda-ketahui</ref>\n**[[Labuan Bajo]] - ([[Komodo Airport]])\n**[[Kupang]] - ([[El Tari International Airport]])\n**[[Maumere]] - ([[Frans Xavier Seda Airport]])\n**[[Ruteng]] - ([[Frans Sales Lega Airport]])\n**[[Semarang]] - ([[Achmad Yani International Airport]])\n**[[Surakarta]] - ([[Adisumarmo International Airport]])<ref>http://m.rri.co.id/surakarta/post/berita/788867/ekonomi/nam_air_pindah_rute_penerbangan_dari_solo_mana_saja_rutenya.html</ref><ref>https://m.solopos.com/nam-air-buka-rute-anyar-dari-bandara-adi-soemarmo-ke-luar-jawa-mana-saja-1046501</ref><ref>https://www.flynamair.com/admin/assets/uploads/images/home_banner/2020-03/terbang-solo-3-en-7161.jpg</ref>\n**[[Surabaya]] - ([[Juanda International Airport]])\n**[[Tambolaka]] - ([[Tambolaka Airport]])\n**[[Waingapu]] - ([[Umbu Mehang Kunda Airport]])\n**[[Yogyakarta]] - ([[Adisucipto International Airport]])<ref>https://www.jogja.tribunnews.com/amp/2013/12/20/nam-air-kini-terbangi-rute-yogyakarta-pontianak</ref><ref>https://www.flynamair.com/about</ref><ref>https://jambi.antaranews.com/berita/308789/seputar-nam-air-yang-patut-anda-ketahui</ref> (Terminated Since 31 March, 2020)\n*'''[[Sumatra]]''' and '''[[Riau Islands]]'''\n**[[Bandar Lampung]] - ([[Radin Inten II Airport]])\n**[[Lubuklinggau]] - ([[Silampari Airport]])\n**[[Palembang]] - ([[Sultan Mahmud Badaruddin II International Airport]])<ref>http://m.rri.co.id/surakarta/post/berita/788867/ekonomi/nam_air_pindah_rute_penerbangan_dari_solo_mana_saja_rutenya.html</ref><ref>https://m.solopos.com/nam-air-buka-rute-anyar-dari-bandara-adi-soemarmo-ke-luar-jawa-mana-saja-1046501</ref><ref>https://www.flynamair.com/admin/assets/uploads/images/home_banner/2020-03/terbang-solo-3-en-7161.jpg</ref>\n**[[Pangkal Pinang]] - ([[Depati Amir Airport]])<ref>http://m.rri.co.id/surakarta/post/berita/788867/ekonomi/nam_air_pindah_rute_penerbangan_dari_solo_mana_saja_rutenya.html</ref><ref>https://m.solopos.com/nam-air-buka-rute-anyar-dari-bandara-adi-soemarmo-ke-luar-jawa-mana-saja-1046501</ref><ref>https://www.flynamair.com/admin/assets/uploads/images/home_banner/2020-03/terbang-solo-3-en-7161.jpg</ref>\n**[[Tanjung Pandan]] - ([[H.A.S. Hanandjoeddin International Airport]])\n*'''[[Kalimantan]]'''\n**[[Banjarmasin]] - ([[Syamsudin Noor Airport]]) <ref>https://www.kompas.com/money/read/2019/04/26/112844326/nam-air-buka-2-rute-baru-di-kalimantan-mulai-1-mei-2019</ref>\n**[[Ketapang (Kalimantan)|Ketapang]] - ([[Rahadi Osman Airport]])<ref>https://www.instagram.com/p/BabSfbRDty5/</ref>\n**[[Palangkaraya]] - ([[Tjilik Riwut Airport]])(begins 29 March 2020)<ref>http://m.rri.co.id/surakarta/post/berita/788867/ekonomi/nam_air_pindah_rute_penerbangan_dari_solo_mana_saja_rutenya.html</ref><ref>https://m.solopos.com/nam-air-buka-rute-anyar-dari-bandara-adi-soemarmo-ke-luar-jawa-mana-saja-1046501</ref>\n**[[Pangkalan Bun]] - ([[Iskandar Airport]])\n**[[Pontianak, Indonesia|Pontianak]] - ([[Supadio International Airport]])<ref>https://www.kompas.com/money/read/2019/04/26/112844326/nam-air-buka-2-rute-baru-di-kalimantan-mulai-1-mei-2019</ref><ref>https://www.flynamair.com/about</ref><ref>https://jambi.antaranews.com/berita/308789/seputar-nam-air-yang-patut-anda-ketahui</ref><ref>https://www.instagram.com/p/BabSfbRDty5/</ref><ref>https://www.jogja.tribunnews.com/amp/2013/12/20/nam-air-kini-terbangi-rute-yogyakarta-pontianak</ref><ref>http://m.rri.co.id/surakarta/post/berita/788867/ekonomi/nam_air_pindah_rute_penerbangan_dari_solo_mana_saja_rutenya.html</ref><ref>https://m.solopos.com/nam-air-buka-rute-anyar-dari-bandara-adi-soemarmo-ke-luar-jawa-mana-saja-1046501</ref><ref>https://www.flynamair.com/admin/assets/uploads/images/home_banner/2020-03/terbang-solo-3-en-7161.jpg</ref>\n**[[Putussibau]] - ([[Pangsuma Airport]])<ref>https://www.instagram.com/p/BabSfbRDty5/</ref>\n**[[Samarinda]] - ([[Aji Pangeran Tumenggung Pranoto Airport]]) <ref>https://www.kompas.com/money/read/2019/04/26/112844326/nam-air-buka-2-rute-baru-di-kalimantan-mulai-1-mei-2019</ref>\n**[[Sampit]] - ([[Sampit Airport]])\n**[[Sintang Regency|Sintang]] - ([[Tebelian Airport]])<ref>https://www.instagram.com/p/BabSfbRDty5/</ref>\n**[[Tarakan]] - ([[Juwata International Airport]]) <ref>https://www.kompas.com/money/read/2019/04/26/112844326/nam-air-buka-2-rute-baru-di-kalimantan-mulai-1-mei-2019</ref>\n*'''[[Sulawesi]]''' and '''[[Maluku Islands|Maluku]]'''\n**[[Ambon, Maluku|Ambon]] - ([[Pattimura Airport]])\n**[[Manado]] - ([[Sam Ratulangi International Airport]])\n**[[Ternate]] - ([[Sultan Babullah Airport]])\n*'''[[West Papua (province)|West Papua]]''' and '''[[Papua (province)|Papua]]'''\n**[[Biak]] - ([[Frans Kaisiepo Airport]])\n**[[Fakfak]] - ([[Fakfak Torea Airport]])\n**[[Jayapura]] - ([[Sentani Airport]])\n**[[Kaimana]] - ([[Utarom Airport]])\n**[[Waisai]] - ([[Marinda Airport]])\n\n;East Timor\n*[[Dili]] - ([[Presidente Nicolau Lobato International Airport]]) <ref> https://m.bisnis.com/amp/read/20151220/98/503517/nam-air-buka-rute-baru-denpasar-dili</ref>\n\n== Fleet ==\n[[File:NAM Air Sintang.jpg|thumb|NAM Air ATR 72-600 at [[Tebelian Airport]], [[Sintang Regency|Sintang]]]]\n[[File:PK-NAP.jpg|thumb|NAM Air Boeing 737-500 at [[Ngurah Rai International Airport]], [[Denpasar]].]]\nThe NAM Air fleet consists of the following aircraft (as of August 2019):<ref>{{cite journal|title=Global Airline Guide 2019 (Part One)|journal=Airliner World|issue=October 2019|page=16}}</ref>\n\n<center>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"3\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse;text-align:center\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Aircraft\n! rowspan=\"2\" |In Service\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Orders \n! colspan=\"3\" |Passengers\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Notes\n|-\n!C\n!Y\n!Total\n|-\n|[[ATR 72|ATR 72-600]]\n|5<ref>https://www.instagram.com/p/BeF1b5jH5r7/</ref>\n|1\n|0\n|72\n|72 \n|\n|-\n|[[Boeing 737 Classic|Boeing 737-500]]\n|11\n|&mdash;\n|8\n|112\n|120\n|\n|-\n!Total\n!16\n!1\n!colspan=\"4\"|\n|}\n</center>\n\nEvery Sriwijaya Air Group plane (which includes NAM Air) has a unique name, which can be seen on the nose section. The names are taken from holy book phrases, places, behaviours, and plants or birds. Examples on NAM Air include \"Bersinar\" (Shiny), \"Kehormatan\" (Honor), and \"Berbagi (Sharing).\n\n==EU aviation blacklist==\n{{main|List of air carriers banned in the European Union}}\nNAM Air was banned from operating in European airspace,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ec.europa.eu/transport/modes/air/safety/air-ban/index_en.htm|title=The EU Air Safety List - Transport|publisher=}}</ref><ref>http://ec.europa.eu/transport/modes/air/safety/air-ban/doc/list_en.pdf</ref> appearing on a list of carriers that did not meet necessary safety standards to fly to airports in the European Union. It was removed from the blacklist, along with every other Indonesian airline on 14 June 2018.<ref>{{cite web |last1=European Commission |title=Aviation Safety: Commission removes all airlines from Indonesia from EU Air Safety List |url=http://europa.eu/rapid/press-release_IP-18-4131_en.htm |website=European Commission - Press Release Database |accessdate=10 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category|NAM Air}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.flynamair.com}}\n\n{{Portalbar|Indonesia|Companies|Aviation}}\n{{Garuda Indonesia}}\n{{Airlines of Indonesia}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sriwijaya Air Destinations}}\n[[Category:Airlines banned in the European Union]]\n[[Category:Airlines of Indonesia]]\n[[Category:Airlines established in 2013]]\n[[Category:2013 establishments in Indonesia]]\n", "name_user": "Meandkancil2020", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eDestinations:NAM Air already Begins Palangkaraya Services since , 29 March 2020.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NAM_Air"}
{"title_page": "Bury a Friend", "text_new": "{{good article}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{short description|2019 single by Billie Eilish}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Bury a Friend\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Billie Eilish]]\n| album      = [[When We All Fall Asleep, Where Do We Go?]]\n| released   = {{start date|2019|1|30}}\n| genre      = <!-- Genres must be sourced -->\n* [[Electronica]]\n* [[synth-pop]]\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=13}}\n| label      =\n* Darkroom\n* [[Interscope Records|Interscope]]\n| writer     =\n* [[Billie Eilish|Billie Eilish O'Connell]]\n* [[Finneas O'Connell]]\n| producer   = Finneas O'Connell\n| prev_title = [[When I Was Older]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title = [[Wish You Were Gay]]\n| next_year  = 2019\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|HUHC9tYz8ik|\"Bury a Friend\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Bury a Friend'''\" is a song by American singer [[Billie Eilish]] from her debut studio album, ''[[When We All Fall Asleep, Where Do We Go?]]'' (2019). It was released as the third [[Single (music)|single]] from the record on January 30, and later serviced to US alternative radio stations on February 19, 2019, with both releases occurring through Darkroom and [[Interscope Records]]. Eilish and her brother [[Finneas O'Connell]] co-wrote the song, with the latter solely producing it. The song was described as [[synth-pop]] and [[electronica]] in press reviews, for which [[Hip hop music|hip hop]] beats, percussion, and a [[synthesizer]] provide [[Minimalism|minimalist]] instrumentation. Within the dark and violent lyrics, Eilish sings from the perspective of a monster under someone's bed. Her vocals are subtle and treated with layers of vocal effects.\n\nUpon release, \"Bury a Friend\" received generally positive reviews from music critics, several of whom praised its dark nature and lyrics. The song was also likened to the music of [[Marilyn Manson (band)|Marilyn Manson]], [[Lorde]] and [[Kanye West]]. It attained commercial success, including reaching number one in Sweden and Latvia. The song further peaked within the top ten in several countries, such as New Zealand, Canada, Australia, and the United Kingdom. [[Music Canada]] awarded it a triple platinum [[Music recording certification|certification]], among others.\n\n[[Michael Chaves (director)|Michael Chaves]] directed the music video for \"Bury a Friend\", which was uploaded to Eilish's [[YouTube]] channel at the same time as the song's first release. The video depicts Eilish involved in several activities, including singing under the bed of British rapper Crooks, who provides uncredited vocals on the song, being pulled by black gloves and walking through a rundown apartment. Critics noted the video's [[Horror fiction|horror]] elements. Eilish promoted the song by performing it live at venues in 2019, including [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival]], [[Glastonbury Festival]] and during her [[When We All Fall Asleep Tour]]. It was also included on the setlist of her 2020 [[Where Do We Go? World Tour]].\n\n==Background and development==\n[[File:Finneas O'Connell 2019 by Glenn Francis.jpg|150px|thumb|Eilish's brother [[Finneas O'Connell]] (''pictured'') contributed to the song's writing and production.<ref name=\"credits\"/>|alt=An image of a blonde-haired man wearing a suit and sunglasses against a purple-red backdrop.]]\nOn January 29, 2019, Billie Eilish formally announced the release of ''When We All Fall Asleep, Where Do We Go?'' and also revealed that she would release a single the next day at 9 AM ([[Pacific Time Zone|PT]]). She further posted a 16-second teaser of the song, featuring her singing while being grabbed and pushed by gloved hands.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.altpress.com/news/billie-eilish-when-we-all-fall-asleep-where-do-we-go/|title=Billie Eilish announces debut album with hauting image|last=Quiles|first=Alyssa|date=January 29, 2019|work=[[Alternative Press (magazine)|Alternative Press]]|access-date=July 21, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190130053323/https://www.altpress.com/news/billie-eilish-when-we-all-fall-asleep-where-do-we-go/|archive-date=January 30, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2019/01/29/billie-eilish-announce-album-tease-song|title=Billie Eilish announces debut album title, says 'new song out tomorrow'|last=Hussein|first=Wandera|date=January 29, 2019|work=[[The Fader]]|access-date=January 31, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190130053239/https://www.thefader.com/2019/01/29/billie-eilish-announce-album-tease-song|archive-date=January 30, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> \"Bury a Friend\" was eventually released on the scheduled date,<ref name=\"credits\"/> having premiered on [[Zane Lowe]]'s [[Beats 1]] show as the day's World Record.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://uproxx.com/music/billie-eilish-bury-a-friend-album-announce/|title=Billie Eilish Debuted A Dark New Song, 'Bury A Friend,' And Shared Details About Her Upcoming Album|last=Gilke|first=Chloe|date=January 30, 2019|publisher=[[Uproxx]]|access-date=January 31, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190131011906/https://uproxx.com/music/billie-eilish-bury-a-friend-album-announce/|archive-date=January 31, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Eilish further made an appearance on [[Annie Mac]]'s Future Sounds show on [[BBC Radio 1]] to discuss the track.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/m000267n|title=Billie Eilish on the phone and Hozier brings the party|publisher=[[BBC]]|access-date=January 31, 2019|date=January 30, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190201021009/https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/m000267n|archive-date=February 1, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> It was serviced to US alternative radio stations on February 19, 2019 by Darkroom and [[Interscope Records]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allaccess.com/alternative/future-releases|title=Future Releases on Alternative Radio Stations, Independent Artist Song Releases|publisher=All Access|access-date=January 31, 2019|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190201100207/https://www.allaccess.com/alternative/future-releases|archivedate=February 1, 2019}}</ref> \"Bury a Friend\" was written by Eilish along with her brother [[Finneas O'Connell]], while production was solely handled by the latter. The song was [[Mastering (music)|mastered]] by John Greenham and [[Mixing (music)|mixed]] by [[Rob Kinelski]], with both also serving as studio personnel.<ref name=\"credits\"/>\n\nThe creation of the song took place in Chicago, which Eilish and her brother were visiting for a [[Lollapalooza]] performance. They attended a studio with a \"[[Swing (jazz performance style)|shuffle beat]]\" in mind, with Eilish drawing a black monster to show her brother what she wanted the song to sound like.<ref name=\"mind\">{{cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kvo_R9eKpVc|title=A Snippet into Billie\u2019s Mind - bury a friend|publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=February 22, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416000012/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kvo_R9eKpVc|archive-date=April 16, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Eilish desired to hear her name at the beginning of the track, for which she texted rapper Calvin (known as Mehki Raine); he ultimately sent Eilish a phone recording for her to use.<ref name=\"mind\"/><ref name=\"nme\"/> The singer discovered the rapper on [[social media]] due to him repeatedly tagging pictures of himself with the caption \"Where's Billie at?\" on her [[Instagram]] comments. She decided to make him her acquaintance and the two soon became friends.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2018/8490017/billie-eilish-jimmie-allen-review-favorite-albums-of-2018|title=Billie Eilish, Anderson .Paak, Jimmie Allen & More Review Their Favorite Albums of 2018|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=December 13, 2018|accessdate=July 21, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190405213801/https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2018/8490017/billie-eilish-jimmie-allen-review-favorite-albums-of-2018|archive-date=April 5, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Composition and lyrical interpretation==\nEilish credited the song for setting the tone for ''When We All Fall Asleep, Where Do We Go?'', stating: \"I immediately knew what it was going to be about, what the visuals were going to be, and everything in terms of how I wanted it to be perceived\".<ref name=\"complex\"/> \"Bury a Friend\" has been described as a [[synth-pop]] and [[electronica]] track in press reviews.<ref name=\"jimmy\">{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8504925/billie-eilish-performs-bury-a-friend-jimmy-kimmel-video|title=Billie Eilish Gives Ominous Performance Of 'Bury a Friend' On 'Jimmy Kimmel': Watch|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=April 1, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|author=Acevedo, Angelica|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190721074252/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8504925/billie-eilish-performs-bury-a-friend-jimmy-kimmel-video|archive-date=July 21, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"director\">{{cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/billie-eilish-bury-a-friend-video-new-lp-786599/|title=Billie Eilish Gets Creepy in New 'Bury a Friend' Video, Details Debut LP|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=January 30, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|author=Exposito, Suzy|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331192844/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/billie-eilish-bury-a-friend-video-new-lp-786599/|archive-date=March 31, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Suzy Exposito of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' called it \"[[Gothic rock|goth]]-[[Rhythm and blues|R&B]]\" reminiscent of [[Marilyn Manson (band)|Marilyn Manson]]'s ''[[Antichrist Superstar]]'' (1996).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-album-reviews/review-billie-eilish-when-we-all-fall-asleep-where-do-we-go-814754/|title=Review: Billie Eilish\u2019s \u2018When We All Fall Asleep, Where Do We Go?\u2019 Is Noir Pop With Bite|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=March 29, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|author=Exposito, Suzy|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190930212734/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-album-reviews/review-billie-eilish-when-we-all-fall-asleep-where-do-we-go-814754/|archive-date=September 30, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The song is moderately fast at 120 [[Tempo|beats per minute]] (BPM), and is written in the key of [[G minor]].<ref name=\"notes\"/> Its [[Minimalism|minimalist]] instrumentation features a [[Hip hop music|hip hop]] and \"galloping\" beat similar to [[Kanye West]]'s \"[[Black Skinhead]]\" (2013).<ref name=\"nme\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hotpress.com/music/billie-eilish-releases-new-single-music-video-22765986|title=Billie Eilish Releases New Single And Music Video|publisher=[[Hotpress.com]]|date=January 31, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|author=Dean, Lucas|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190721074249/https://www.hotpress.com/music/billie-eilish-releases-new-single-music-video-22765986|archive-date=July 21, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/2019/04/08/711076801/wily-and-clever-billie-eilishs-debut-album-sounds-like-no-one-else?t=1555277337703&t=1567619163928|title=Wily And Clever, Billie Eilish's Debut Album Sounds Like No One Else|publisher=[[NPR]]|date=April 8, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|author=Tucker, Ken|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190904174838/https://www.npr.org/2019/04/08/711076801/wily-and-clever-billie-eilishs-debut-album-sounds-like-no-one-else%3Ft%3D1555277337703%26t%3D1567619163928|archive-date=September 4, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Burks, Tosten |title=Billie Eilish Announces Debut Album, Releases \"bury a friend\" |url=https://www.spin.com/2019/01/billie-eilish-bury-a-friend-album-release-date/ |website=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]] |accessdate=January 27, 2020 |date=January 30, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127004603/https://www.spin.com/2019/01/billie-eilish-bury-a-friend-album-release-date/ |archive-date=January 27, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> \"Rumbling\" percussion, \"scattered\" synth melodies, screams, and a screeching recording of an [[Orthodontics|orthodontist]] shaving off Eilish's dental brace attachments are also included.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thefader.com/2019/01/30/billie-eilish-new-song|title=Billie Eilish shares new song and video \"bury a friend\"|work=[[The Fader]]|date=January 30, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|author=Hussein, Wandera|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190131092851/https://www.thefader.com/2019/01/30/billie-eilish-new-song|archive-date=January 31, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"paper\">{{cite news|url=https://www.papermag.com/billie-eilish-bury-friend-2627553314.html?rebelltitem=1#rebelltitem1|title=Billie Eilish Is Here to Haunt You With a New Video|work=[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]|date=January 30, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|author=Love, Michael|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190904171039/https://www.papermag.com/billie-eilish-bury-friend-2627553314.html?rebelltitem=1#rebelltitem1|archive-date=September 4, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.popsugar.co.uk/entertainment/What-Meanings-Behind-Billie-Eilish-Songs-46074252|title=Billie Eilish and Her Brother Finneas Explain the Captivating Creative Process Behind Her Music|publisher=[[PopSugar]]|date=April 25, 2019|accessdate=July 21, 2019|author=Cubit, Brea|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190721212035/https://www.popsugar.co.uk/entertainment/What-Meanings-Behind-Billie-Eilish-Songs-46074252|archive-date=July 21, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Charlie Harding of ''[[Vox (website)|Vox]]'' pointed out \"a broken song form with strange alternate [[verse (music)|verse]]s and a [[bridge (music)|bridge]] placed untraditionally after a verse, rather than immediately following a penultimate [[Refrain|chorus]]. The effect is destabilizing, and yet still accessible to the average listener\".<ref name=\"vox\"/> The melody presented during the chorus has been likened to [[the Doors]]' \"[[People Are Strange]]\" (1967),<ref name=\"nme2\">{{cite news|title=Get on board with Billie Eilish \u2013 her 10 best songs so far|url=https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-blogs/billie-eilish-best-songs-2450318|work=[[NME]]|date=March 8, 2019|accessdate=July 21, 2019|author=Smith, Thomas|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190508231419/https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-blogs/billie-eilish-best-songs-2450318|archive-date=May 8, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and sonically described as \"innocuous as a childhood rhyme\", contrasting the rest of the song.<ref name=\"consequence\">{{cite news|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2019/02/song-of-the-week-billie-eilish-asks-the-big-questions-on-bury-a-friend/|title=Song of the Week: Billie Eilish Asks the Big Questions on \"Bury a Friend\"|work=[[Consequence of Sound]]|date=February 1, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|author=Dzubay, Laura|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191024012719/https://consequenceofsound.net/2019/02/song-of-the-week-billie-eilish-asks-the-big-questions-on-bury-a-friend/|archive-date=October 24, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAccording to Eilish, the track's \"dark\" and \"violent\" lyrics<ref name=\"redefine\">{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8498076/billie-eilish-bury-a-friend-pop-star|title=Billie Eilish Is Inches Away From Redefining Pop Stardom in 2019|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=February 12, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|author=Unterberger, Andrew|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190721074242/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8498076/billie-eilish-bury-a-friend-pop-star|archive-date=July 21, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> are written from the perspective of \"the monster under your bed. Anything could be the monster \u2014 it could be someone you love so much that it\u2019s taking over your life. I think love and terror and hatred are all the same thing\".<ref name=\"rolling\">{{cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/billie-eilish-album-songs-interview-tour-tickets-797040/|title=Billie Eilish\u2019s Teenage Truths|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=February 22, 2019|accessdate=July 21, 2019|author=Weiner, Jonah|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190628014749/https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/billie-eilish-album-songs-interview-tour-tickets-797040/|archive-date=June 28, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Laura Dzubay of ''[[Consequence of Sound]]'' interpreted: \"[Eilish] assumes the position of a monster there to haunt somebody (a lover or herself [...]).\"<ref name=\"consequence\"/> ''[[The Michigan Daily]]''{{'s}} Samantha Cathie thought the fact that the singer was \"hat[ing] herself\" mirrored in the lines: \"Like I wanna drown, like I wanna end me\u201d and \"Honestly I thought that I would be dead by now\".<ref name=\"michigan\"/> Eilish asks several questions during the song's refrain: \"What do you want from me? Why don\u2019t you run from me? Why aren\u2019t you scared of me? Why do you care for me? When we all fall asleep, where do we go?\".<ref name=\"vox\">{{cite news|url=https://www.vox.com/culture/2019/4/18/18412282/who-is-billie-eilish-explained-coachella-2019|title=Billie Eilish, the neo-goth, chart-topping 17-year-old pop star, explained|work=[[Vox (website)|Vox]]|date=April 18, 2019|accessdate=July 21, 2019|author=Harding, Charlie|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190913234243/https://www.vox.com/culture/2019/4/18/18412282/who-is-billie-eilish-explained-coachella-2019|archive-date=September 13, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"consequence\"/><ref name=\"idolator\">{{cite news|url=https://www.idolator.com/7691604/billie-eilish-bury-a-friend-video?firefox=1&Exc_D_LessThanPoint002_p1=1|title=Billie Eilish\u2019s Hot Streak Continues With Haunting Single, \"Bury A Friend\"|publisher=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|date=January 30, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|author=Nied, Mike}}</ref> Further lyrics include: \"Step on the glass, staple your tongue/ Bury a friend, try to wake up/ Cannibal class, killing the son/ Bury a friend, I wanna end me\".<ref name=\"jimmy\"/> The singer's \"soft\" vocals in \"Bury a Friend\" range between the notes of F#<sub>3</sub> and B\u266d<sub>4</sub>.<ref name=\"notes\">{{cite news|url=https://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0193111|title=Billie Eilish \"Bury a Friend\" Sheet Music|publisher=Musicnotes.com|accessdate=July 21, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190204174418/https://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0193111|archive-date=February 4, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"network\">{{cite news|url=https://themusicnetwork.com/sotd-billie-eilishs-bury-a-friend-is-a-devilish-masterpiece/|title=SOTD: Billie Eilish\u2019s \u2018bury a friend\u2019 is a devilish masterpiece|date=February 6, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|work=[[The Music Network]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331231711/https://themusicnetwork.com/sotd-billie-eilishs-bury-a-friend-is-a-devilish-masterpiece/|archive-date=March 31, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> They are treated with layers of vocal effects, and a \"playful trickery [is used] in each hook\".<ref name=\"nme\"/> Eilish described the track as a \"near-whispered sing-song duet between [her] and a distorted version of herself\".<ref name=\"redefine\"/>\n\n==Reception==\n[[File:Kanye West @ MoMA 4.jpg|thumb|left|The song's production has been likened to that of [[Kanye West]]'s (''pictured'') album ''[[Yeezus]]''.<ref name=\"redefine\"/><ref name=\"yeezus\"/>|alt=An image of a man singing into a microphone against red light.]]\nUpon release, \"Bury a Friend\" received generally positive reviews from [[Music journalism|music critics]]. Several publications saw the song as her best single, as well as a highlight of ''When We All Fall Asleep, Where Do We Go?''.<ref name=\"nme\"/><ref name=\"nme2\"/><ref name=\"uproxx\">{{cite news|url=https://uproxx.com/music/best-new-pop-billie-eilish-ally-brooke/2/|title=All The Best New Pop Music From This Week|publisher=[[Uproxx]]|date=February 4, 2019|accessdate=July 21, 2019|author=Gilke, Chloe}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/when-we-all-fall-asleep-where-do-we-go-mw0003250262|title=When We All Fall Asleep, Where Do We Go? \u2013 Billie Eilish|author=Yeung, Neil Z.|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=September 4, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329172745/https://www.allmusic.com/album/when-we-all-fall-asleep-where-do-we-go-mw0003250262|archive-date=March 29, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/mar/29/billie-eilish-when-we-all-fall-asleep-where-do-we-go-review|title=Billie Eilish: When We All Fall Asleep, Where Do We Go? review \u2013 thrilling Gen Z terror-pop|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=March 29, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|author=Snapes, Laura|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329115454/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/mar/29/billie-eilish-when-we-all-fall-asleep-where-do-we-go-review|archive-date=March 29, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> It was likened to [[Lorde]]'s \"[[Royals (song)|Royals]]\" (2013),<ref name=\"nme2\"/> as well as its production to that on West's ''[[Yeezus]]'' (2013).<ref name=\"redefine\"/><ref name=\"yeezus\">{{cite news|url=https://www.gq.com/story/4-point-5-songs-billie-eilish-lucy-dacus-dawn-richard|title=The 4.5 Songs You Need to Hear This Week|work=[[GQ]]|date=January 31, 2019|accessdate=July 21, 2019|author=Carley, Brennan|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190721074247/https://www.gq.com/story/4-point-5-songs-billie-eilish-lucy-dacus-dawn-richard|archive-date=July 21, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Jenkins, Craig |title=Billie Eilish Is the Future |url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/03/billie-eilish-when-we-all-fall-asleep-album-review.html |website=[[New York (magazine)|Vulture]] |accessdate=27 January 2020 |date=29 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200122020354/https://www.vulture.com/2019/03/billie-eilish-when-we-all-fall-asleep-album-review.html |archive-date=January 22, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Newstead, Al |title=First Spin: Billie Eilish's goes horror pop on 'bury a friend', announces debut album |url=https://www.abc.net.au/triplej/news/musicnews/billie-eilish-new-song-video-bury-a-friend-album-release-2019/10765770 |website=[[ABC Online]] |accessdate=27 January 2020 |date=31 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190516134613/https://www.abc.net.au/triplej/news/musicnews/billie-eilish-new-song-video-bury-a-friend-album-release-2019/10765770 |archive-date=May 16, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Thomas Smith of ''[[NME]]'' saw \"Bury a Friend\" as \"a sizeable middle finger to anyone who expected a twinkly ballad befitting to her lone EP, 2017's ''[[Don't Smile at Me]]''\", as well as a \"statement\" for \"vocalising the uncertainties and inquisitions of a generation ready to make their mark\".<ref name=\"nme\"/> ''[[DIY (magazine)|DIY]]''{{'s}} Lisa Wright labelled the song \"intoxicating and intriguing \u2013 aka exactly what you want from a new star\".<ref name=\"diy\"/> Chloe Gilke of [[Uproxx]] praised the \"full of bizarre, screechy flourishes and dips into the nightmarish\" and claimed that \"somehow the song\u2019s lyrics are just as specific and creepy\".<ref name=\"uproxx\"/> Similarly, an editor for ''[[The Music Network]]'' commented on the song's \"sinister [nature] in name and \"lyric\" and claimed that it is \"unsettling\", despite there being \"something\" tranquil and thoughtful about it\".<ref name=\"network\"/> ''[[The Independent]]''{{'s}} Roisin O'Connor praised \"Bury a Friend\" as \"excellent\", and also noted its \"imperious\" and \"anthemic quality\". She further commented on the successful use of Eilish's \"formula\": \"murmuring in cool low tones over a pulsing beat\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/billie-eilish-album-review-when-we-all-fall-asleep-stream-tracklist-tour-a8843596.html|title=When We All Fall Asleep, Where Do We Go? Review|work=[[The Independent]]|author=O'Connor, Roisin|date=March 29, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329083103/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/billie-eilish-album-review-when-we-all-fall-asleep-stream-tracklist-tour-a8843596.html|archive-date=March 29, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In a lukewarm review, Samantha Cantie of ''The Michigan Daily'' saw the song as \"slightly disappointing\". She wrote: \"[A] letdown is her seeming embrace of making an abnormal creation because it\u2019s cool, as opposed to creating something with the beauty of sound as a priority\", and elaborated, stating: \"The track is choppy, cutting from different melodies quite quickly \u2013 these melodies bump, but they\u2019re fleeting\".<ref name=\"michigan\">{{cite news|url=https://www.michigandaily.com/section/arts/eilish-goes-haunted-and-hackneyed-bury-friend|title=Eilish goes haunted and hackneyed on \u2018bury a friend\u2019|work=[[The Michigan Daily]]|date=February 6, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|author=Cantie, Samantha|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190412165418/https://www.michigandaily.com/section/arts/eilish-goes-haunted-and-hackneyed-bury-friend|archive-date=April 12, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Joe Coscarelli noted an \"odd structure\" and \"nightmare lyrics\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/01/arts/music/billie-eilish-bury-a-friend.html|title=A Staple Gun. A Dental Drill. See How Billie Eilish Made a Haunted Pop Hit|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=April 1, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|author=Coscarelli, Joe|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190906081211/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/01/arts/music/billie-eilish-bury-a-friend.html|archive-date=September 6, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n\"Bury a Friend\" attained commercial success. It debuted at number 74 on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] before moving 60 places to number 14 with 29.1 million streams and 18,000 downloads sold in its first full week of tracking, becoming Eilish's highest peak on the chart at the time, before surpassed by \"[[Bad Guy (Billie Eilish song)|Bad Guy]]\" (2019).<ref name=\"Hot 100 peak\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8497755/ariana-grande-7-rings-hot-100-number-one-third-week|title=Ariana Grande's '7 Rings' Spends Third Week Atop Billboard Hot 100, Marshmello Makes Fortnite-Fueled Flight to No. 2|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=February 11, 2019|accessdate=February 12, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401011851/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8497755/ariana-grande-7-rings-hot-100-number-one-third-week|archive-date=April 1, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.altpress.com/news/billie-eilish-billboard-chart-bury-a-friend/|title=Billie Eilish scores first No. 1 on Alternative Digital Song Sales chart|work=[[Alternative Press (magazine)|Alternative Press]]|last=Shoemaker|first=Whitney|date=February 16, 2019|accessdate=February 17, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331204657/https://www.altpress.com/news/billie-eilish-billboard-chart-bury-a-friend/|archive-date=March 31, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The song also became the singer's first number one on a ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' radio airplay chart, topping the US [[Alternative Songs]] chart in May 2019. This made Eilish only the tenth solo woman in a lead role to reach number one in the chart's three-decade history.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8512389/billie-eilish-first-airplay-chart-nuber-1-bury-a-friend|title=Billie Eilish Scores First Airplay Chart No. 1 as 'Bury a Friend' Tops Alternative Songs|last=Rutherford|first=Kevin|date=May 20, 2019|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|access-date=July 31, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190721074242/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8512389/billie-eilish-first-airplay-chart-nuber-1-bury-a-friend|archive-date=July 21, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In the United Kingdom, \"Bury a Friend\" reached number six, making it Eilish's first top ten in the country.<ref name=\"UKS\" /> The song has further peaked at number one in Sweden and Latvia,<ref name=\"Latvia\"/><ref name=\"Sweden\"/> and within the top ten in countries such as New Zealand, Australia and Canada.<ref name=\"New Zealand\"/><ref name=\"Australia\"/><ref name=\"Canada\"/> It has been awarded several [[Music recording certification|certifications]], most notably triple platinum by [[Music Canada]] for sales of 240,000 copies.<ref name=\"cert\"/><ref name=\"cert2\"/>\n\n==Music video==\nAn accompanying music video for \"Bury a Friend\" was uploaded to Eilish's official [[YouTube]] channel on January 30, 2019.<ref name=\"video\">{{cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HUHC9tYz8ik|title=Billie Eilish - bury a friend|publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=January 30, 2019|accessdate=September 5, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190904222313/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HUHC9tYz8ik|archive-date=September 4, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> It was directed by [[Michael Chaves (director)|Michael Chaves]] in the span of a day.<ref name=\"director\"/><ref name=\"idolator\"/> The clip contains [[Horror fiction|horror]] elements, which have led to it being regarded by reviewers as \"creepy\" and \"haunting\".<ref name=\"nme\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-radar/billie-eilish-bury-a-friend-review-listen-2440682|title=Billie Eilish\u2019s horror-lovin\u2019 \u2018Bury A Friend\u2019 is a haunting new track from our recent cover star|work=[[NME]]|date=January 30, 2019|accessdate=July 21, 2019|author=Smith, Thomas|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329150602/https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-radar/billie-eilish-bury-a-friend-review-listen-2440682|archive-date=March 29, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"complex\"/> Eilish explained: \"I had this idea where I\u2019m naked. Like an abduction-type thing, completely not in control, just a helpless body, and people putting syringes up my arms and in my neck. That\u2019s one of people\u2019s biggest fears\u2014needles\u2014and that\u2019s what I\u2019ve been doing recently: honing in on people\u2019s fears\".<ref name=\"rolling\"/> The visual begins with Mehki Raine awaking from a nightmare while a \"seemingly possessed\" Eilish lies under his bed. The singer subsequently walks through a rundown apartment complex before she is pulled and prodded by hands covered with black [[latex]] gloves. Eilish is then injected with syringes before she \"mysteriously\" disappears under Mehki's bed,<ref name=\"complex\">{{cite news|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2019/01/billie-eilish-bury-a-friend-video|title=Billie Eilish Announces Debut Album, Drops Horror-Inspired Video for \"bury a friend\"|work=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|date=January 30, 2019|accessdate=July 21, 2019|author=Espinoza, Joshua|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331204449/https://www.complex.com/music/2019/01/billie-eilish-bury-a-friend-video|archive-date=March 31, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> with scenes also seeing the singer levitating with \"broken-doll\" feet.<ref name=\"paper\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8495771/billie-eilish-bury-a-friend-music-video|title=Billie Eilish Unveils Haunting Video for New Single 'bury a friend': Watch|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=January 30, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|author=Rowley, Glenn|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190405225636/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8495771/billie-eilish-bury-a-friend-music-video|archive-date=April 5, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Critics have likened the visual to several works released by fellow artists, including [[Alice Glass]],<ref name=\"diy\">{{cite news|url=http://diymag.com/2019/02/01/tracks-black-midi-the-chemical-brothers-billie-eilish-more|title=Tracks: Black Midi, The Chemical Brothers, Billie Eilish & more|work=[[DIY (magazine)|DIY]]|author=Wright, Lisa|date=February 1, 2019|accessdate=July 21, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190727090955/http://diymag.com/2019/02/01/tracks-black-midi-the-chemical-brothers-billie-eilish-more|archive-date=July 27, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Chris Cunningham]] and [[Floria Sigismondi]].<ref name=\"redefine\"/> Others compared it to the films ''[[Suspiria (2018 film)|Suspiria]]'' (2018) and ''[[Get Out]]'' (2017),<ref name=\"uproxx\"/><ref name=\"nz\"/> the television series ''[[The Haunting of Hill House (TV series)|The Haunting of Hill House]]'',<ref name=\"nz\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/entertainment/news/article.cfm?c_id=1501119&objectid=12199082|title=Billie Eilish's new music video is a horror show|work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]|date=January 31, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190829134357/https://www.nzherald.co.nz/entertainment/news/article.cfm?c_id=1501119&objectid=12199082|archive-date=August 29, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Stephen King]]'s 1977 novel ''[[The Shining (novel)|The Shining]]''.<ref name=\"paper\"/>\n\n==Live performances and other usage==\n[[File:Billie Eilish at Pukkelpop Festival - 18 AUGUST 2019 (10).jpg|thumb|250px|Eilish performing \"Bury a Friend\" during [[Pukkelpop]] in August 2019.|alt=Image of a woman singing into a microphone. She sports green-black hair and clothing and stands against a black backdrop.]] \nEilish performed the song on [[BBC Radio 1]] in February 2019,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6yULE0lDJjU|title=Billie Eilish - bury a friend on Radio 1|publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=February 27, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190525014743/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6yULE0lDJjU|archive-date=May 25, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and on ''[[Jimmy Kimmel Live!]]'' in March. For the latter performance, the singer sang on a dark, smoke-filled stage and \"summon[ed] a large cloth that swung behind her, casting a monster-like shadow while she bent over backwards\". She wore a baggy black sweater and shorts, alongside a neon green frowny face print\".<ref name=\"jimmy\"/> In April, May and June, Eilish performed the track at the [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2019/04/14/entertainment/billie-eilish-coachella-trnd/index.html|title=Billie Eilish played Coachella for the first time and the audience went wild|publisher=[[CNN]]|date=April 14, 2019|accessdate=March 16, 2020|author=Kaur, Harmeet|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190417014117/https://edition.cnn.com/2019/04/14/entertainment/billie-eilish-coachella-trnd/index.html|archive-date=April 17, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[BBC Radio 1's Big Weekend]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7UAOqtoZiLs|title=Billie Eilish - bury a friend (Radio 1's Big Weekend 2019)|publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=May 25, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190704133851/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7UAOqtoZiLs|archive-date=July 4, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and the [[Glastonbury Festival]], respectively.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2019/music/news/billie-eilish-glastonbury-performance-1203256737/|title=Billie Eilish Mesmerizes Glastonbury Crowd With Life-Affirming Performance|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=July 1, 2019|accessdate=July 14, 2019|author=Saval, Marina|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190711095213/https://variety.com/2019/music/news/billie-eilish-glastonbury-performance-1203256737/|archive-date=July 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> She later sang it during [[Pukkelpop]] in August,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hln.be/showbizz/muziek/festivals/hysterie-tijdens-billie-eilish-maar-perfect-is-het-nog-lang-niet~a03449ff/?referer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2F|title=Hysterie tijdens Billie Eilish, maar perfect is het nog lang niet|trans-title=Hysteria during Billie Eilish concert, but it isn't perfect yet|work=[[Het Laatste Nieuws]]|date=August 18, 2019|accessdate=August 25, 2019|language=Dutch}}</ref> and included \"Bury a Friend\" on the setlist of her [[When We All Fall Asleep Tour]] (2019) and [[Where Do We Go? World Tour]] (2020) tours.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rnz.co.nz/national/programmes/nat-music/audio/2018692292/review-billie-eilish-at-spark-arena-a-shared-dream|title=Review: Billie Eilish at Spark Arena \u2013 \"a shared dream\"|publisher=[[Radio New Zealand]]|date=April 25, 2019|accessdate=March 16, 2020|author=Saw, Yadana}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2020/03/billie-eilish-where-do-we-go-world-tour-setlist-video/|title=Billie Eilish Launches \"Where Do We Go? World Tour\"|publisher=Young, Alex|work=[[Consequence of Sound]]|date=March 10, 2020|accessdate=March 16, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311152106/https://consequenceofsound.net/2020/03/billie-eilish-where-do-we-go-world-tour-setlist-video/|archive-date=March 11, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe song was featured in the television series ''[[The Society (TV series)|The Society]]''. Kaitlin Reilly noted similarity between the lyrics and the series' plot.<ref name=\"refinery\">{{cite news|url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2019/05/233625/billie-eilish-society-trailer-song-meaning-spoiler|title=Did This Billie Eilish Song Tease A Big Spoiler For The Society?|publisher=[[Refinery29]]|date=May 24, 2019|accessdate=July 21, 2019|author=Reilly, Kaitlin|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190608030606/https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2019/05/233625/billie-eilish-society-trailer-song-meaning-spoiler|archive-date=June 8, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Zeds Dead]] remixed \"Bury a Friend\" to acclaim from ''Billboard''{{'s}} Kat Bein, who included it in her 12 Best Billie Eilish Remixes list.\nShe stated that the remix takes the original song and \"runs it through a few sonic filters [while] [m]oody ambience gives way to fat bass synths [...] [,] old-school [[dubstep]] wub-dubs [and] [...] drums [which] kick up in a slow-down [[UK garage]] style in the later half\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/8486224/billie-eilish-songs-best-remixes-list|title=The 12 Best Billie Eilish Remixes|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=March 29, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019|author=Bein, Kat|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190721074252/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/dance/8486224/billie-eilish-songs-best-remixes-list|archive-date=July 21, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Credits and personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref name=\"credits\">{{cite news|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/106538977/track/106538979|title=When We All Fall Asleep, Where Do We Go? (Bury a Friend) \u2013 Billie Eilish|publisher=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|date=March 29, 2019|accessdate=July 21, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329124823/https://listen.tidal.com/album/106538977/track/106538979|archive-date=March 29, 2019|url-status=live}} ''Note: Access the 'Credits' button.''</ref>\n\n*[[Billie Eilish]] \u2013 vocals, songwriter\n*[[Finneas O'Connell]] \u2013 producer, songwriter\n*John Greenham \u2013 mastering engineer, studio personnel\n*Rob Kinelski \u2013 mixing, studio personnel\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Argentina ([[Argentina Hot 100]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/billie-eilish/chart-history/billboard-argentina-hot-100|title=Billie Eilish Chart History (Billboard Argentina Hot 100)|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=August 19, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190819025053/https://www.billboard.com/music/billie-eilish/chart-history/billboard-argentina-hot-100|archive-date=August 19, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| 85\n|-\n{{single chart|Australia|3|artist=Billie Eilish|song=Bury a Friend|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 9, 2019|refname=\"Australia\"}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|6|artist=Billie Eilish|song=Bury a Friend|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 13, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|13|artist=Billie Eilish|song=Bury a Friend|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 2, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia|42|artist=Billie Eilish|song=Bury a Friend|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 23, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Canada|10|artist=Billie Eilish|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 9, 2019|refname=\"Canada\"}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Czechdigital|3|year=2019|week=06|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 12, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Denmark|8|artist=Billie Eilish|song=Bury a Friend|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 17, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Finland|4|artist=Billie Eilish|song=Bury a Friend|rowheader=true|accessdate=February 10, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|France|82|artist=Billie Eilish|song=Bury a Friend|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 4, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Germany2|14|songid=1838398|artist=Billie Eilish|song=Bury a Friend|rowhea