{"title_page": "Abhishek Singh (artist)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}}\n{{notability|date=June 2018}}\n[[File:Abhi-devi.jpg|thumb|Artist Abhishek Singh in front of his Goddess Paintings. (Left) Triveni-the three aspects of the river (Right) Bhagvati-Shakti creating the Gods.]]\n'''Abhishek Singh''' (born July 1982) is an Indian<ref>{{Citation|last=Asia Society Texas Center|title=Abhishek Singh in Conversation with Julie Romain|date=2014-09-23|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9DLK0srhvpE&t=924s|accessdate=2017-05-25}}</ref> [[Graphic novelist]] acclaimed for his unique interpretations of myths and ancient philosophies instigating environmental themes, universal identity and spiritual oneness.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://solpurpose.com/2015/01/27/shiva-brush-abhishek-singh/|title=Shiva Through the Brush of Abhishek Singh|last=Bromley|first=Brian|date=2015-01-27|website=SolPurpose|access-date=2017-05-25}}</ref>\n\nAbhishek was born in [[Gwalior]] and studied Animation and Film Design at India's [[National Institute of Design]]. He is the writer and illustrator for graphic novel ''Krishna-a journey within''<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.amazon.com/KRISHNA-Journey-Within-Abhishek-Singh/dp/160706653X|title=KRISHNA: A Journey Within|last=Singh|first=Abhishek|date=2012-12-18|publisher=Image Comics|isbn=9781607066538|location=Berkeley, Calif.|language=English}}</ref> published by [[Image Comics|Image comics]], he is the first Indian descent creator to be published by them in the history of North American comic-books. He was the illustrator for the [[Ramayan 3392 A.D.|''Ramayana 3392 A.D'']] and [[India Authentic (comics)|''India Authentic comics'']]. His work spans fine-art exhibitions, comic-books, animation and virtual reality films, original futuristic fables and re-imaginations of the mythological stories of India.{{Citation needed|date=August 2017}}\n\n[[File:Abhishek-Painting Shiva.jpg|thumb|Abhishek painting Shiva at the ghtas of Varanasi for the social impact project \"An ode to Ganges\"]]\nHis paintings, drawings and digital works have featured in the following exhibitions: \"Heroes and Villains: the Battle for Good in India\u2019s Comics\" at the [[Lacma|Los Angeles County Museum of Art (LACMA);]], \"Transcendent Deities of India: The Everyday Occurrence of the Divine\" at the [[Asia Society]] in Houston, Texas; at the ghats of [[Varanasi]], India; a social impact project organized by Ojas Art Foundation, other exhibitions include \"Dhyana Roopa\" at the Academy of Fine Arts and Literature in Delhi, \"India Imagined\" sponsored by the Nirula Family Art Trust and at the visionary Fractal Gallery at Burning Man sponsored by the Black Rock Arts Foundation.\n\nRecently, he made a virtual reality film for Deepak Chopra.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://blog.wevr.com/deepak-chopra-pioneers-wellness-benefits-of-vr-with-finding-your-true-self-858|title=Deepak Chopra Pioneers Wellness Benefits of VR With Finding Your True Self \u2013 The Wevr Blog|website=blog.wevr.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-05-30}}</ref> The film explores VR as a therapeutic platform of the future where conventional medicine can be substituted with immersive experiences.\n\nAbhishek has also designed and developed animation properties for Cartoon network, Honk-kong and India, He served as an art-director on UTV's [[Arjun: The Warrior Prince|Arjun-the warrior prince]] for a brief time. He was invited to design a small sequence for [[Juanjo Guarnido]]'s \"Freak Kitchen\"<ref>{{Citation|last=Juanjo Guarnido|title=Freak Kitchen - Freak of the Week - Official Music Video|date=2014-10-28|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y2vzBdIejVY|accessdate=2017-05-25}}</ref> animated video and has served a concept artist on several un-announced live-action and animated projects.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://abhishekart.com/ Abhishek Singh, Official Site]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Singh, Abhishek}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Indian graphic novelists]]\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:People from Gwalior]]\n[[Category:Novelists from Madhya Pradesh]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}}\n{{notability|date=June 2018}}\n[[File:Abhi-devi.jpg|thumb|Artist Abhishek Singh in front of his Goddess Paintings. (Left) Triveni-the three aspects of the river (Right) Bhagvati-Shakti creating the Gods.]]\n'''Abhishek Singh''' (born July 1982) is an Indian<ref>{{Citation|last=Asia Society Texas Center|title=Abhishek Singh in Conversation with Julie Romain|date=2014-09-23|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9DLK0srhvpE&t=924s|accessdate=2017-05-25}}</ref> [[Graphic novelist]] acclaimed for his unique interpretations of myths and ancient philosophies instigating environmental themes, universal identity and spiritual oneness.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://solpurpose.com/2015/01/27/shiva-brush-abhishek-singh/|title=Shiva Through the Brush of Abhishek Singh|last=Bromley|first=Brian|date=2015-01-27|website=SolPurpose|access-date=2017-05-25}}</ref>\n\nAbhishek was born in [[Gwalior]] and studied Animation and Film Design at India's [[National Institute of Design]]. He is the writer and illustrator for graphic novel ''Krishna-a journey within''<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.amazon.com/KRISHNA-Journey-Within-Abhishek-Singh/dp/160706653X|title=KRISHNA: A Journey Within|last=Singh|first=Abhishek|date=2012-12-18|publisher=Image Comics|isbn=9781607066538|location=Berkeley, Calif.|language=English}}</ref> published by [[Image Comics|Image comics]], he is the first indian descent creator to be published by them in the history of North American comic-books. He was the illustrator for the [[Ramayan 3392 A.D.|''Ramayana 3392 A.D'']] and [[India Authentic (comics)|''India Authentic comics'']]. His work spans fine-art exhibitions, comic-books, animation and virtual reality films, original futuristic fables and re-imaginations of the mythological stories of India.{{Citation needed|date=August 2017}}\n\n[[File:Abhishek-Painting Shiva.jpg|thumb|Abhishek painting Shiva at the ghtas of Varanasi for the social impact project \"An ode to Ganges\"]]\nHis paintings, drawings and digital works have featured in the following exhibitions: \"Heroes and Villains: the Battle for Good in India\u2019s Comics\" at the [[Lacma|Los Angeles County Museum of Art (LACMA);]], \"Transcendent Deities of India: The Everyday Occurrence of the Divine\" at the [[Asia Society]] in Houston, Texas; at the ghats of [[Varanasi]], India; a social impact project organized by Ojas Art Foundation, other exhibitions include \"Dhyana Roopa\" at the Academy of Fine Arts and Literature in Delhi, \"India Imagined\" sponsored by the Nirula Family Art Trust and at the visionary Fractal Gallery at Burning Man sponsored by the Black Rock Arts Foundation.\n\nRecently, he made a virtual reality film for Deepak Chopra.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://blog.wevr.com/deepak-chopra-pioneers-wellness-benefits-of-vr-with-finding-your-true-self-858|title=Deepak Chopra Pioneers Wellness Benefits of VR With Finding Your True Self \u2013 The Wevr Blog|website=blog.wevr.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-05-30}}</ref> The film explores VR as a therapeutic platform of the future where conventional medicine can be substituted with immersive experiences.\n\nAbhishek has also designed and developed animation properties for Cartoon network, Honk-kong and india, He served as an art-director on UTV's [[Arjun: The Warrior Prince|Arjun-the warrior prince]] for a brief time. He was invited to design a small sequence for [[Juanjo Guarnido]]'s \"Freak Kitchen\"<ref>{{Citation|last=Juanjo Guarnido|title=Freak Kitchen - Freak of the Week - Official Music Video|date=2014-10-28|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y2vzBdIejVY|accessdate=2017-05-25}}</ref> animated video and has served a concept artist on several un-announced live-action and animated projects.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://abhishekart.com/ Abhishek Singh, Official Site]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Singh, Abhishek}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Indian graphic novelists]]\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:People from Gwalior]]\n[[Category:Novelists from Madhya Pradesh]]\n", "name_user": "Dan Koehl", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:clean up,typo(s) fixed: indian \u2192 Indian (2)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abhishek_Singh_(artist)"}
{"title_page": "Tamil Rockers", "text_new": "{{short description|BitTorrent website}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox website\n| name = Tamil Rockers\n| logo = Tamilrockers logo.jpg\n| url = <!-- Per WP:COPYVIOEL it's prohibited to link to sites containing copyright violations. -->\n| type = Torrent index, [[Magnet URI scheme|magnet links]] provider, [[Peer-to-peer]]\n| language = English\n| launch_date = {{Start date and age|2011}}\n| revenue = Advertisements\n| current_status = Active\n}}{{filesharing sidebar}}\n\n'''Tamil Rockers''' is a torrent website which facilitates the illegal distribution of copyrighted material, including television shows, movies, music and videos.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/tamilrockers-how-does-the-website-work-who-are-uploading-movies/articleshow/66602806.cms |title=Tamilrockers: How does the website work? Who are uploading movies? |last=Prabhakar |first=Siddharth |date=29 November 2018 |website=[[The Times of India]] |archive-url=https://archive.today/20190612080015/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/tamilrockers-how-does-the-website-work-who-are-uploading-movies/articleshow/66602806.cms |archive-date=12 June 2019 |url-status=live |access-date=18 February 2019 }}</ref> The site allows visitors to search for and download copyrighted material with the help of [[Magnet URI scheme|magnet links]] and [[Torrent file|torrent]] files, which facilitate [[peer-to-peer]] [[file sharing]]. In [[India]], [[Internet service provider|ISPs]] have been ordered to block access to the website.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://newstodaynet.com/index.php/2019/02/05/actor-vishal-meets-chief-minister-seeks-action-against-tamilrockers/ |title=Actor Vishal meets Chief Minister, seeks action against Tamilrockers |date=5 February 2019 |website=[[The News Today (India)|The News Today]] |access-date=18 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/how-karthik-subbarajs-petta-team-fighting-tamil-rockers-and-other-online-pirates-94915 |title=How Karthik Subbaraj's 'Petta' team is fighting Tamil Rockers |last=Shekar |first=Anjana |date=January 12, 2019 |website=[[The News Minute]] |access-date=18 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/block-tamilrockers-and-piracy-websites-delhi-high-court-to-internet-service-providers-1580094-2019-08-12|title=Block TamilRockers and piracy websites: Delhi High Court to Internet Service Providers|last=DelhiAugust 12|first=Press Trust of India New|last2=August 12|first2=2019UPDATED|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2019-08-30|last3=Ist|first3=2019 18:47}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/delhi-hc-directs-internet-service-providers-to-block-tamilrockers-for-unauthorised-movie-screening-2268223.html|title=Delhi HC Directs Internet Service Providers to Block Tamilrockers for Unauthorised Movie Screening|website=News18|access-date=2019-08-30}}</ref> The website continues operation by switching to a series of new web addresses.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.oneindia.com/india/2-0-leaked-why-is-it-so-hard-to-stop-the-tamilrockers-2816221.html |title=2.0 leaked: Why is it so hard to stop the Tamilrockers? |date=1 December 2018 |website=[[Oneindia]] |access-date=18 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ekumkum.com/blog/tamilrockers-tamil-movie-download/|title=Tamilrockers Tamil Movie Download 2020 Tamilrockers Hindi Movies Download|last=Ahir|first=Kumkum|website=Latest News Today {{!}} All India News In Hindi|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref> Aside from its traditional list of pirate sites, apps, and hosting providers, the movie industry group [[MPAA]] now lists Tamil Rockers as one of the [[notorious markets]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://torrentfreak.com/mpa-adds-1xbet-and-baidu-to-latest-piracy-threat-report/|title=MPA Adds 1XBET and Baidu to Latest Piracy Threat Report|date=2019-10-13|website=TorrentFreak|language=en|access-date=2019-10-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://torrentfreak.com/images/Motion_Picture_Association_2019_Notorious_Markets_OCR.pdf|title=MPA\u2019s full report|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nTamil Rockers is the tenth most popular torrent site in [[TorrentFreak]]'s Top 10 Most Popular Torrent Sites of 2020 list.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://torrentfreak.com/top-10-most-popular-torrent-sites-of-2020-200105/|title=Top 10 Most Popular Torrent Sites of 2020|date=2020-01-05|website=TorrentFreak|language=en|access-date=2020-01-31}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nTamil Rockers was a [[bootleg recording]] network which was founded in 2011 and later became a public torrent website that links to pirated copies of Indian films in addition to Hollywood movies dubbed into regional languages along with the original English audio.\n\nOn 14 March 2018, three men said to be behind the site were arrested. One of the men was believed to be the site administrator.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/kerala-police-arrest-5-piracy-3-tamilrockers-and-2-dvd-rockers-78008|website=www.thenewsminute.com|access-date=2019-08-30|title=Kerala police arrest 5 for piracy: 3 from Tamilrockers and 2 from DVD rockers|date=15 March 2018}}</ref> On 23 May 2019, more members of Tamilrockers were arrested in [[Coimbatore]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Members-of-piracy-website-TamilRockers-arrested/articleshow/55887838.cms|title=TamilRockers: Members of piracy website Tamil Rockers arrested - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-08-30}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n[[Category:Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:BitTorrent websites]]\n[[Category:Notorious markets]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|BitTorrent website}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox website\n| name = Tamil Rockers\n| 